cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on understanding stances people hold on controversial topics within populations, and examines Twitter coverage and real-world polling data sets. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses computationally detecting controversial topics and measuring contention. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper examines controversy and contention within populations. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possibility as the paper may touch on the security and privacy implications of analyzing Twitter data. 
- cs.DL (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper discusses modeling contention from a mathematical standpoint.
